   139вҶ’## Versions
   141вҶ’A "version" is described by the `v2.0.0` specification found at
   142вҶ’<https://semver.org/>.
   143вҶ’
   144вҶ’A leading `"="` or `"v"` character is stripped off and ignored.
   145вҶ’Support for stripping a leading "v" is kept for compatibility with `v1.0.0` of the SemVer
   146вҶ’specification but should not be used anymore.
   147вҶ’
   148вҶ’## Ranges
   150вҶ’A `version range` is a set of `comparators` that specify versions
   151вҶ’that satisfy the range.
   152вҶ’
   153вҶ’A `comparator` is composed of an `operator` and a `version`.  The set
   154вҶ’of primitive `operators` is:
   155вҶ’
   156вҶ’* `<` Less than
   157вҶ’* `<=` Less than or equal to
   158вҶ’* `>` Greater than
   159вҶ’* `>=` Greater than or equal to
   160вҶ’* `=` Equal.  If no operator is specified, then equality is assumed,
   161вҶ’  so this operator is optional but MAY be included.
   162вҶ’
   163вҶ’For example, the comparator `>=1.2.7` would match the versions
   164вҶ’`1.2.7`, `1.2.8`, `2.5.3`, and `1.3.9`, but not the versions `1.2.6`
   165вҶ’or `1.1.0`. The comparator `>1` is equivalent to `>=2.0.0` and
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   184вҶ’### Prerelease Tags
   186вҶ’If a version has a prerelease tag (for example, `1.2.3-alpha.3`) then
   187вҶ’it will only be allowed to satisfy comparator sets if at least one
   188вҶ’comparator with the same `[major, minor, patch]` tuple also has a
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   219вҶ’#### Prerelease Identifiers
   221вҶ’The method `.inc` takes an additional `identifier` string argument that
   222вҶ’will append the value of the string as a prerelease identifier:
   223вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   250вҶ’#### Prerelease Identifier Base
   252вҶ’The method `.inc` takes an optional parameter 'identifierBase' string
   253вҶ’that will let you let your prerelease number as zero-based or one-based.
   254вҶ’Set to `false` to omit the prerelease number altogether.
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   279вҶ’### Advanced Range Syntax
   281вҶ’Advanced range syntax desugars to primitive comparators in
   282вҶ’deterministic ways.
   283вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   287вҶ’#### Hyphen Ranges `X.Y.Z - A.B.C`
   289вҶ’Specifies an inclusive set.
   290вҶ’
   291вҶ’* `1.2.3 - 2.3.4` := `>=1.2.3 <=2.3.4`
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   306вҶ’#### X-Ranges `1.2.x` `1.X` `1.2.*` `*`
   308вҶ’Any of `X`, `x`, or `*` may be used to "stand in" for one of the
   309вҶ’numeric values in the `[major, minor, patch]` tuple.
   310вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   324вҶ’#### Tilde Ranges `~1.2.3` `~1.2` `~1`
   326вҶ’Allows patch-level changes if a minor version is specified on the
   327вҶ’comparator.  Allows minor-level changes if not.
   328вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   341вҶ’#### Caret Ranges `^1.2.3` `^0.2.5` `^0.0.4`
   343вҶ’Allows changes that do not modify the left-most non-zero element in the
   344вҶ’`[major, minor, patch]` tuple.  In other words, this allows patch and
   345вҶ’minor updates for versions `1.0.0` and above, patch updates for
      вҶ’вҖҰ
